*Vercel Web Analytics Setup*

The Vercel Web Analytics has been successfully installed and configured for this Next.js App Router project.

**Installation Steps Completed:**

1. **Package Installation:**
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics@1.6.1` via npm
   - Package added to package.json dependencies

2. **Analytics Integration:**
   - Added Analytics component to `src/app/layout.tsx` (root layout)
   - Import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
   - Component placed in the `<body>` tag: `<Analytics />`

3. **Configuration:**
   - Following Next.js App Router best practices from official Vercel documentation
   - Analytics component is loaded globally for all pages
   - No additional configuration required - works automatically when deployed to Vercel

**To Enable Analytics:**

1. Deploy this project to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate analytics tracking
4. Analytics will start tracking page views automatically

**Verification:**

After deployment, you can verify analytics is working by:
- Checking the browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
- Viewing the Analytics dashboard in your Vercel project settings

**Framework:** Next.js 14 (App Router)
**Package Manager:** npm
**Analytics Package Version:** 1.6.1

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation and Next.js App Router conventions.
